.SH "NAME"
Dist::Zilla::Role::TextTemplate \- something that renders a Text::Template template string
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 6.017
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Plugins implementing TextTemplate may call their own \f(CW"fill_in_string"\fR
method to render templates using Text::Template.
.SH "ATTRIBUTES"
.IX Header "ATTRIBUTES"
.SS "delim"
.IX Subsection "delim"
This attribute (which can't easily be set!) is a two-element array reference
returning the Text::Template delimiters to use.  It defaults to \f(CW\*(C`{{\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`}}\*(C'\fR.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS "fill_in_string"
.IX Subsection "fill_in_string"
.Vb 1
\&  my $rendered = $plugin\->fill_in_string($template, \e%stash, \e%arg);
.Ve
.PP
This uses Text::Template to fill in the given template using the variables
given in the \f(CW%stash\fR.  The stash becomes the \s-1HASH\s0 argument to Text::Template,
so scalars must be scalar references rather than plain scalars.
.PP
\&\f(CW%arg\fR is dereferenced and passed in as extra arguments to Text::Template's
\&\f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR routine.
